{
  "page": "Old Mother",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">The Old Mother</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nThe Old Mother</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Band_of_Nine\" title=\"Band of Nine\">Band of Nine</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (Mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>The Old Mother</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Pirate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pirate\">pirate</a> queen who became one of the infamous <a href=\"/index.php/Band_of_Nine\" title=\"Band of Nine\">Band of Nine</a>, the instigators of the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Ninepenny_Kings\" title=\"War of the Ninepenny Kings\">War of the Ninepenny Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The name of the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Old_Mother%27s_Son\" title=\"Old Mother&#39;s Son\">Old Mother's Son</a></i>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Ships\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ships\">galley</a> in the fleet of <a href=\"/index.php/Salladhor_Saan\" title=\"Salladhor Saan\">Salladhor Saan</a>, seems to be inspired by her.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_Mother&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Band_of_Nine\" title=\"Band of Nine\">Band of Nine</a> were a group of merchants, sellswords and pirates who joined together to carve kingdoms out for themselves.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Old_Mother&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Jaehaerys II.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404205330\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.090 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.329 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 464/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10380/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 3280/2097152 bytes\nTemplate a